Navigation on command line

Ctrl + a # Move to the start of line
Ctrl + e # Move to the end of line
Alt + f # Move forward a word (a word contains alphabets and digits, no symbols)
Alt + b # Move backward a word 
Ctrl + l # Clear the screen 

Ctrl+U #clears the whole line
Ctrl+K #deletes from cursor to the end of the line
Ctrl+W #deletes the word before the cursor only 
Ctrl+f #forward character by character
Ctrl+b #move backward character by character
Ctl+R #Reverse index search (allows you to type part of a command. searches in reverse order through command history for a matching command)
